OL,3,CFewer exams, lessons on AI and
OL,4,Cmortgages: England's school curriculum
OL,5,Cshake-up
OL,7,FEngland is an "international outlier"
OL,8,Fwith the number of exams for students
OL,9,Fof this age, with only Singapore
OL,10,Fhaving a comparable amount, according
OL,11,Fto curriculum review leader Professor
OL,12,FBecky Francis.
OL,14,F"We do want to try and bring that
OL,15,Fdown," she said. "It's a very intense
OL,16,Fand elongated time, as anyone who's
OL,17,Fbeen a parent of GCSE-age pupils
OL,18,Fknows, but we don't want to trade
OL,19,Fstandards and reliability."
